  "body": "See this screenshot from the designs, the blue circle with the \"1\" in it informs the user that they have one @mention in the #beginners channel\r\n\r\n![2021-09-21 10_37_20-Window](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/22846356/134148623-f51ca4b4-f2d9-488a-b46c-0b95a99fc8a8.png)\r\n\r\nHowever it looks like this is currently broken, the @mention emblem only appears on the *Community* icon (correct) but doesn't appear next to the channel name as shown in the design above (incorrect).  See screenshot below, here I've been @mentioned in the #test-channel and I haven't visited this channel since I was @mentioned so the @mention emblem should be shown next to this channel name but it isn't.\r\n\r\n![2021-09-21 10_26_49-Window](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/22846356/134149133-1b51f6b3-5f28-4e8c-801d-779fd5c62e69.png)\r\n\r\n-------------\r\nDesired resoltuion:\r\n\r\n- @mention emblems should be shown both on the community icon and after the channel name. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
